  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ukraine Tensions: No Child Forgotten</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Eight years of war in East Ukraine means there are thousands of Internally Displaced Persons (IDP). As tensions rise nationwide, the economy is threatened, as are millions of people in high-risk areas. Families of children with disabilities - usually single mothers - suffer most. Affording regular medical treatments in peacetime on state support is hard; in times of unrest, it is impossible. We help IDP and high-risk zone families of children with disabilities access essential medical care.</narrative>
  </description>
